gle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 14, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104fxp1665702959450.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fxp1665702959450.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/fxp1665702959450.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"fxp1665702959450\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Lightweight Sessions\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Lightweight sessions allow multiple user sessions within a single database connection. </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"fxp1665702959450__context_w3569ab1b5b1_w3570ab1b5_w3571ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fxp1665702959450__p_d56360e1_d56361e1_d56362e1\">This functionality is provided by Oracle through the\n            Oracle Call Interface (OCI). Each lightweight session uniquely identifies a connected\n            user (authenticated by a database password) without the overhead of a separate database\n            connection. Lightweight sessions preserve the identity of the real user through the\n            middle tier, which is authorized to act on behalf of the client by the Oracle\n            administrator. To authorize an application server to proxy a client, use the GRANT\n            CONNECT THROUGH clause of the ALTER USER statement in Oracle. With this clause you can\n            also specify roles that the application server is permitted to activate when connecting\n            as the client. Lightweight sessions can be specified via the assignment file as\n            follows:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fxp1665702959450__p_d56363e1_d56364e1_d56365e1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">$</code><var class=\"keyword varname\">PathName</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">=ORA:{</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Database</var>}<code class=\"ph codeph\">|</code>{<var class=\"keyword varname\">UserName</var>}{<code class=\"ph codeph\">#</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">ClientUsername</var>}<code class=\"ph codeph\">|</code>{<var class=\"keyword varname\">Password</var>}</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fxp1665702959450__p_d56366e1_d56367e1_d56368e1\">Once a lightweight session path is identified, Oracle will:</p>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step\" id=\"fxp1665702959450__li_d25772e1_d25773e1_d25774e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Check if a 'master' database connection (Database/UserName/Password) exists and is connected (if not, then a new \"master\" database connection is created).\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step\" id=\"fxp1665702959450__li_d25775e1_d25776e1_d25777e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Create a lightweight session (ClientUsername) via the 'master' database connection.\n </span>\n</li></ol></section>\n<section class=\"section result body required-cleanup-multiple-ol-elements-in-topic-body\" id=\"fxp1665702959450__result_w3572ab1b5b5_w3573ab1b5_w3574ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"fxp1665702959450__p_d56369e1_d56370e1_d56371e1\">By default, master database connections are closed\n            when all lightweight sessions are ended. To keep master connections open, even when\n            paths are closed, use the <code class=\"ph codeph\">disable lws close</code> connector option.</p>\n         Master database connections and their lightweight sessions are always created via the OCI\n         interface. By default, the first logon path to Oracle is created using the Pro*C/C++\n         precompiler interface, but if the first logon path is a lightweight session path then the\n         OCI interface is used.</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cui1665702732182.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>disable lws close</a><p>Keep the master connection open after ending a lightweight session</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527727\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527727\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Lightweight Sessions Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Lightweight Sessions Lightweight sessions allow multiple user sessions within a single database connection. This functionality is provided by Oracle through the Oracle Call Interface (OCI). Each lightweight session uniquely identifies a connected user (authenticated by a database password) without the overhead of a separate database connection. Lightweight sessions preserve the identity of the real user through the middle tier, which is authorized to act on behalf of the client by the Oracle administrator. To authorize an application server to proxy a client, use the GRANT CONNECT THROUGH clause of the ALTER USER statement in Oracle. With this clause you can also specify roles that the application server is permitted to activate when connecting as the client. Lightweight sessions can be specified via the assignment file as follows: $ PathName =ORA:{ Database } | { UserName }{ # ClientUsername } | { Password } Once a lightweight session path is identified, Oracle will: Check if a 'master' database connection (Database/UserName/Password) exists and is connected (if not, then a new \"master\" database connection is created). Create a lightweight session (ClientUsername) via the 'master' database connection. By default, master database connections are closed when all lightweight sessions are ended. To keep master connections open, even when paths are closed, use the disable lws close connector option. Master database connections and their lightweight sessions are always created via the OCI interface. By default, the first logon path to Oracle is created using the Pro*C/C++ precompiler interface, but if the first logon path is a lightweight session path then the OCI interface is used. Related Links disable lws close Keep the master connection open after ending a lightweight session Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}